{"title_page": "Maha Al-Saati", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Maha Al-Saati<br><big>\u0645\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a\u064a</big>\n| image              = Maha Al-Saati.png\n| birth_place        = [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| alma mater         = [[Simon Fraser University]]\n| occupation         = Independent Filmmaker, University Professor\n| years_active       = 2016\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Maha Al-Saati''' (also known as '''Maha Alsaati''', '''Maha Zeini Al-Saati'''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=maha+zeini+al-saati&source=bl&ots=EO8_LSmG5c&sig=ACfU3U1P-X0pBuyt6e8pu5_k0IvTiyb_bA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjsqoT_vfLnAhVfRhUIHV6ACMkQ6AEwCXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=maha%20zeini%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref>, [[Arabic language|Arabic]]: \u0645\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a\u064a) is a Saudi Arabian female filmmaker<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://studio300.transy.edu/digital-media/creators/|title=Creators \u2013 Studio 300|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iscm.org/catalogue/composers/shields-alice|title=Shields, Alice|last=ISCM|date=2019-07-31|website=ISCM|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moviemaker.com/newfilmmakers-la-maha-al-saati-mary-lyn-chambers-and-more/|title=NewFilmmakers LA: Maha Al Saati, Mary Lyn Chambers, Ludovica Isidori, David Plasencia, and More|last=LA|first=NewFilmmakers|date=2019-08-23|website=MovieMaker Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> and university professor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iau.edu.sa/en/colleges/college-of-design/faculty/dr-maha-al-saati|title=Dr. Maha Al-Saati {{!}} Imam Abdulrahman Bin Faisal University|website=www.iau.edu.sa|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Janak|first=Edward A.|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?hl=en&lr=&id=WFYYDgAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA127&dq=maha+al-saati+protagonist&ots=wXoMqhB1uD&sig=kTJk98HExkxXU4A4XwYp5qymoSE&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati%20protagonist&f=false|title=Educating through Popular Culture: You're Not Cool Just Because You Teach with Comics|last2=Sourdot|first2=Ludovic A.|date=2017-03-01|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=978-1-4985-4918-9|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PR6&dq=maha+al-saati+Death+within+the+Text:+Social,+Philosophical+and+Aesthetic+Approaches+to+Literature,+edited+by+Adriana+Teodorescu&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjR_IOF-vHnAhXMA2MBHThHAh4Q6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref> who has taught both in Vancouver, Canada and Saudi Arabia<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound|title=Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound|last=Adlakha|first=Siddhant|date=2017-10-04|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iau.edu.sa/en/colleges/college-of-design/faculty/dr-maha-al-saati|title=Dr. Maha Al-Saati {{!}} Imam Abdulrahman Bin Faisal University|website=www.iau.edu.sa|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>. Her filmmaking style has been described as [[Avant-garde]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iscm.org/catalogue/composers/shields-alice|title=Shields, Alice|last=ISCM|date=2019-07-31|website=ISCM|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> and experimental<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://studio300.transy.edu/digital-media/creators/|title=Creators \u2013 Studio 300|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kawa-news.com/en/maha-el-saati-the-fantastic-ufo-from-saudi-experimental-cinema/|title=Maha El Saati, the fantastic UFO from Saudi experimental cinema|date=2019-02-11|website=KAWA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>.\n\n== Filmmaking Career ==\nAl-Saati is interested in exploring issues of gender, religion and Arab social norms in her films <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound|title=Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound|last=Adlakha|first=Siddhant|date=2017-10-04|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. has started her filmmaking career with short films such as ''\"Fear: Audibly\" (2017),'' which screened at [[Fantastic Fest]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fantasticfest.com//films/fear-audibly|title=FEAR: AUDIBLY|website=Fantastic Fest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound|title=Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound|last=Adlakha|first=Siddhant|date=2017-10-04|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://womenwriteaboutcomics.com/2017/09/fantastic-shorts-by-women-at-fantastic-fest/|title=Fantastic Shorts by Women at Fantastic Fest|date=2017-09-30|website=WWAC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> and the [[Arab World Institute]]'s Arab Cinema Festival in Paris under the French title ''\"La Peur: sonore\"'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imarabe.org/fr/cinema/la-peur-sonore|title=La Peur : sonore|date=2018-06-11|website=Institut du monde arabe|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. Her short film ''\"Hair: The Story of Grass\" (2018)\",'' explores the topic of body hair and beauty standards in the Arab World<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rdvcanada.ca/en/product/hair-the-story-of-grass/|title=Hair: The Story of Grass {{!}} Canadian Audiovisual Production|website=RDVCanada.ca|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>, and has screened at [[Fantastic Fest]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fantasticfest.com//films/hair-the-story-of-grass|title=HAIR: THE STORY OF GRASS|website=Fantastic Fest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2018/09/05/announcing-fantastic-fests-2018-shorts-programming|title=Announcing Fantastic Fest\u2019s 2018 Shorts Programming|last=Monson|first=Leigh|date=2018-09-05|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>, [[Slamdance Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slamdance2019.eventive.org/schedule/5c1c0bd934d66c00225a9ea6|title=Hair: The Story of Grass|last=|first=|date=|website=Slamdance 2019|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/steven-soderbergh-to-receive-2019-founders-award-at-slamdance-festival/|title=Steven Soderbergh to Receive Founders Award at Slamdance Festival|date=2018-12-11|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> New Filmmakers LA Monthly Film Festival<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newfilmmakersla.com/events/event/monthly-film-festival-july-27th-2019/|title=Monthly Film Festival \u2013 July 27th, 2019|website=LA Film Festival NewFilmmakers Los Angeles|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> and the [[Red Sea International Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.redseafilmfest.com/film?id=79|title=Hair: The Story of Grass - RedSeaFF2020|last=Apps|first=77|website=www.redseafilmfest.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. Her short film ''\"Cycle of Apples\" (2019)'' screened at New Filmmakers LA Monthly Film festival, which was hosted by The [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] in partnership with Arab Film and Media Institute (AFMI)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newfilmmakersla.com/events/event/monthly-film-festival-december-14th-2019/|title=Monthly Film Festival \u2013 December 14th, 2019|website=LA Film Festival NewFilmmakers Los Angeles|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. The film is a collaboration with American electronic opera composer [[Alice Shields]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iscm.org/catalogue/composers/shields-alice|title=Shields, Alice|last=ISCM|date=2019-07-31|website=ISCM|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://studio300.transy.edu/digital-media/creators/|title=Creators \u2013 Studio 300|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>.\n\n\n\nAl-Saati's feature film project \"A Trip to Disney\" is in development with the Red Sea Film Lodge (part of Saudi Arabia's [[Red Sea International Film Festival]]), in partnership with Italy's [[TorinoFilmLab]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.torinofilmlab.it/news/640-announcing-the-12-selected-projects-for-the-red-sea-lodge-2019|title=Announcing the 12 selected projects for the Red Sea Lodge 2019! {{!}} TorinoFilmLab|website=www.torinofilmlab.it|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>''.'' She is one of the female directors that account for one-third of the 12 selected for the Red Sea Lodge, the festival said<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/saudis-red-sea-international-film-festival-unveils-debut-lab-selection/5143374.article|title=Saudi's Red Sea International Film Festival unveils debut lab selection|last=Goodfellow2019-10-01T15:55:00+01:00|first=Melanie|website=Screen|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/saudi-arabia-red-sea-festival-projects-in-development-1203353478/|title=Saudi Arabia\u2019s Red Sea Festival Announces Projects in Development|last=Vivarelli|first=Nick|last2=Vivarelli|first2=Nick|date=2019-10-01|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Film Title\n!Arabic Title\n!Year\n!Screenings\n|-\n|Elo's Nest\n|\u0639\u0634 \u0625\u064a\u0644\u0648\n|2016\n|The 3rd Saudi Film Festival\n|-\n|Fear: Audibly\n|\u0627\u0644\u062e\u0648\u0641: \u0635\u0648\u062a\u064a\u0627\n|2017\n|Fantastic Fest, The Arab Cinema Festival at the Arab World Institute in Paris, The 4th Saudi Film Festival\n|-\n|Hair: The Story of Grass\n|\u0634\u0639\u0631: \u0642\u0635\u0629 \u0639\u0634\u0628\n|2018\n|Fantastic Fest, Slamdance, HollyShorts, Casablana Film Festival, The Red Sea International Film Festival, The 5th Saudi Film Festival\n|-\n|Cycle of Apples\n|\u062f\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u062a\u0641\u0627\u062d\n|2019\n|Oaxaca FilmFest, New Filmmakers LA\n|}\n\n== Research ==\nAl-Saati holds a PhD in Interactive Arts and Technology, from [[Simon Fraser University]] (SFU), [[Surrey, British Columbia]], [[Canada]]<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=maha+zeini+al-saati&source=bl&ots=EO8_LSmG5c&sig=ACfU3U1P-X0pBuyt6e8pu5_k0IvTiyb_bA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjsqoT_vfLnAhVfRhUIHV6ACMkQ6AEwCXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=maha%20zeini%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite thesis|title=The architectural image: space, movement and myth|url=https://summit.sfu.ca/item/13638|publisher=Communication, Art & Technology: School of Interactive Arts and Technology|date=2013-07-22|degree=Thesis|language=en|first=Maha Zeini|last=Al-Saati}}</ref>. Her PhD thesis is titled: ''\"The Architectural Image: Space, Movement and Myth\"'' (2013)<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Al-Saati|first=Maha Zeini|title=The Architectural Image: Space, Movement and Myth|url=https://www.academia.edu/7577363/The_Architectural_Image_Space_Movement_and_Myth|journal=PhD Thesis, The School of Interactive Arts and Technology, Simon Fraser University (SFU), Canada.|language=en}}</ref>, and falls within research that intersects architecture with film<ref>{{Cite journal|last=\u00a0Al-Saati, Maha Zeini; David Botta and Robert Woodbury|first=|date=|title=Moving in filmic spaces: Relating camera movements to spatial archetypes in architectural animations|url=http://papers.cumincad.org/cgi-bin/works/paper/caadria2012_013|journal=Proceedings of the 17th International Conference on Computer Aided Architectural Design Research in Asia|volume=|pages=Chennai 25-28 April 2012|via=Chennai 25-28 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Al-Saati|first=Maha Zeini; David Botta and Robert Woodbury|date=2012|title=Architects on architectural film and animation|url=http://papers.cumincad.org/cgi-bin/works/Show?caadria2012_021|journal=Proceedings of the 17th International Conference on Computer Aided Architectural Design Research in Asia / Chennai 25-28 April 2012, pp. 637\u2013646|publisher=CUMINCAD}}</ref>. She is also a researcher who has written about the intersection of media, religion and culture<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=maha+zeini+al-saati&source=bl&ots=EO8_LSmG5c&sig=ACfU3U1P-X0pBuyt6e8pu5_k0IvTiyb_bA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjsqoT_vfLnAhVfRhUIHV6ACMkQ6AEwCXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=maha%20zeini%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref> in her works: ''\u201cThe Protagonist Does Not Die Anymore: The Influence of the Death Narrative on Popular Saudi Culture\u201d''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PR6&dq=maha+al-saati+Death+within+the+Text:+Social,+Philosophical+and+Aesthetic+Approaches+to+Literature,+edited+by+Adriana+Teodorescu&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjR_IOF-vHnAhXMA2MBHThHAh4Q6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref>''; \"A Question of Relevance: Teaching with Sci-Fi and Fantasy Film in a Saudi University\"''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Janak|first=Edward A.|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?hl=en&lr=&id=WFYYDgAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA127&dq=maha+al-saati+protagonist&ots=wXoMqhB1uD&sig=kTJk98HExkxXU4A4XwYp5qymoSE&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati%20protagonist&f=false|title=Educating through Popular Culture: You're Not Cool Just Because You Teach with Comics|last2=Sourdot|first2=Ludovic A.|date=2017-03-01|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=978-1-4985-4918-9|language=en}}</ref>; and the journal article ''\"Assassin's Creed : A Multi-Cultural Read\"''<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Seif El-Nasr|first=Magy|last2=Al-Saati|first2=Maha|last3=Niedenthal|first3=Simon|last4=Milam|first4=David|date=2008|title=Assassin's Creed : A Multi-Cultural Read|url=http://muep.mau.se/handle/2043/12753|journal=Loading . . .;3|volume=2|issn=1923-2691}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Winston|first=Diane|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=MCCja27G0AAC&pg=PA241&lpg=PA241&dq=The+Oxford+Handbook+of+Religion+and+the+American+News+Media+maha+al-saati&source=bl&ots=JTS1BfUQdE&sig=ACfU3U31GPn0jUDaYQ3aOw3tSyCpOR2j2g&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjn08azl_TnAhVz8uAKHax6A8cQ6AEwAXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=The%20Oxford%20Handbook%20of%20Religion%20and%20the%20American%20News%20Media%20maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=The Oxford Handbook of Religion and the American News Media|date=2012-09-06|publisher=OUP USA|isbn=978-0-19-539506-8|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Young|first=Helen|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=eCg_CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT207&dq=maha+al-saati&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiSoZjQl_TnAhVFA2MBHXxmBrsQ6AEIQTAD#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=The Middle Ages in Popular Culture: Medievalism and Genre|date=2015-07-08|publisher=Cambria Press|isbn=978-1-62196-748-4|language=en}}</ref>. She has a book with French author Lily Valette ''\u201cDans le sens du poil arabe\" (2020) [English: In the Direction of Arab Hair]'' which compares the social attitudes towards body hair in Arab versus Western culture<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.lalibrairie.com/livres/le-poil-arabe_0-6236267_9791093315171.html|title=Livre : Dans le sens du poil arabe \u00e9crit par Maha Al-Saati et Lily Valette - Orients|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.culture.leclerc/livre-u/arts-culture--societe-u/sciences-humaines-u/ethnologie-u/le-poil-arabe-9791093315171-pr|title=Dans le sens du poil arabe|last=E.Leclerc|first=Dans le sens du poil arabe-Lily Valette- 9791093315171- Espace Culturel|website=Espace Culturel E. Leclerc|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gibert.com/le-poil-arabe-11464541.html|title=Ldans le sens du poil arabe|website=www.gibert.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>.\n\n== Extra Links ==\n\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vi0NOdfzv08 France24 Arabic's interview with Maha Al-Saati on Fear: Audibly | July 10, 2018]\n* [https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound Birth.Movies.Death: Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound By Siddhant Adlakha | October 4, 2017\u00a0]\n* [https://filmthreat.com/reviews/hair-the-story-of-grass/ Film Threat: HAIR: THE STORY OF GRASS By Enrique Acosta | September 26, 2019]\n* [https://kawa-news.com/en/maha-el-saati-the-fantastic-ufo-from-saudi-experimental-cinema/ Maha El Saati, the fantastic UFO from Saudi experimental cinema By Kawa News | February 11, 2019]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HEkEUIv-jGY MovieMaker's Stage 5 interview with Maha Al-Saati on Hair: The Story of Grass | August 20, 2019]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mFL4qwtXUMU&list=PLWaYWJqhe6ajHt-dCIa17ZoX9H5-5QYmL&index=1 MovieMaker's Stage 5 interview with vocalist Zeina Nassereddine on Maha Al-Saati's Cycle of Apples | March 10, 2020]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{morecat|date=April 2020}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Al-Saati, Maha}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Maha Al-Saati<br><big>\u0645\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a\u064a</big>\n| image              = Maha Al-Saati.png\n| birth_place        = [[Saudi Arabia]]\n| alma mater         = [[Simon Fraser University]]\n| occupation         = Independent Filmmaker, University Professor\n| years_active       = 2016\u2013present\n}}\n\n'''Maha Al-Saati''' (also known as '''Maha Alsaati''', '''Maha Zeini Al-Saati'''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=maha+zeini+al-saati&source=bl&ots=EO8_LSmG5c&sig=ACfU3U1P-X0pBuyt6e8pu5_k0IvTiyb_bA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjsqoT_vfLnAhVfRhUIHV6ACMkQ6AEwCXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=maha%20zeini%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref>, [[Arabic language|Arabic]]: \u0645\u0647\u0627 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0627\u0639\u0627\u062a\u064a) is a Saudi Arabian female filmmaker<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://studio300.transy.edu/digital-media/creators/|title=Creators \u2013 Studio 300|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iscm.org/catalogue/composers/shields-alice|title=Shields, Alice|last=ISCM|date=2019-07-31|website=ISCM|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moviemaker.com/newfilmmakers-la-maha-al-saati-mary-lyn-chambers-and-more/|title=NewFilmmakers LA: Maha Al Saati, Mary Lyn Chambers, Ludovica Isidori, David Plasencia, and More|last=LA|first=NewFilmmakers|date=2019-08-23|website=MovieMaker Magazine|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> and university professor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iau.edu.sa/en/colleges/college-of-design/faculty/dr-maha-al-saati|title=Dr. Maha Al-Saati {{!}} Imam Abdulrahman Bin Faisal University|website=www.iau.edu.sa|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Janak|first=Edward A.|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?hl=en&lr=&id=WFYYDgAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA127&dq=maha+al-saati+protagonist&ots=wXoMqhB1uD&sig=kTJk98HExkxXU4A4XwYp5qymoSE&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati%20protagonist&f=false|title=Educating through Popular Culture: You're Not Cool Just Because You Teach with Comics|last2=Sourdot|first2=Ludovic A.|date=2017-03-01|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=978-1-4985-4918-9|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PR6&dq=maha+al-saati+Death+within+the+Text:+Social,+Philosophical+and+Aesthetic+Approaches+to+Literature,+edited+by+Adriana+Teodorescu&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjR_IOF-vHnAhXMA2MBHThHAh4Q6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref> who has taught both in Vancouver, Canada and Saudi Arabia<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound|title=Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound|last=Adlakha|first=Siddhant|date=2017-10-04|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iau.edu.sa/en/colleges/college-of-design/faculty/dr-maha-al-saati|title=Dr. Maha Al-Saati {{!}} Imam Abdulrahman Bin Faisal University|website=www.iau.edu.sa|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>. Her filmmaking style has been described as [[Avant-garde]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iscm.org/catalogue/composers/shields-alice|title=Shields, Alice|last=ISCM|date=2019-07-31|website=ISCM|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> and experimental<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://studio300.transy.edu/digital-media/creators/|title=Creators \u2013 Studio 300|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kawa-news.com/en/maha-el-saati-the-fantastic-ufo-from-saudi-experimental-cinema/|title=Maha El Saati, the fantastic UFO from Saudi experimental cinema|date=2019-02-11|website=KAWA|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>.\n\n== Filmmaking Career ==\nAl-Saati is interested in exploring issues of gender, religion and Arab social norms in her films <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound|title=Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound|last=Adlakha|first=Siddhant|date=2017-10-04|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. has started her filmmaking career with short films such as ''\"Fear: Audibly\" (2017),'' which screened at [[Fantastic Fest]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fantasticfest.com//films/fear-audibly|title=FEAR: AUDIBLY|website=Fantastic Fest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound|title=Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound|last=Adlakha|first=Siddhant|date=2017-10-04|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://womenwriteaboutcomics.com/2017/09/fantastic-shorts-by-women-at-fantastic-fest/|title=Fantastic Shorts by Women at Fantastic Fest|date=2017-09-30|website=WWAC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> and the [[Arab World Institute]]'s Arab Cinema Festival in Paris under the French title ''\"La Peur: sonore\"'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.imarabe.org/fr/cinema/la-peur-sonore|title=La Peur : sonore|date=2018-06-11|website=Institut du monde arabe|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. Her short film ''\"Hair: The Story of Grass\" (2018)\",'' explores the topic of body hair and beauty standards in the Arab World<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rdvcanada.ca/en/product/hair-the-story-of-grass/|title=Hair: The Story of Grass {{!}} Canadian Audiovisual Production|website=RDVCanada.ca|language=en-CA|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>, and has screened at [[Fantastic Fest]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fantasticfest.com//films/hair-the-story-of-grass|title=HAIR: THE STORY OF GRASS|website=Fantastic Fest|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2018/09/05/announcing-fantastic-fests-2018-shorts-programming|title=Announcing Fantastic Fest\u2019s 2018 Shorts Programming|last=Monson|first=Leigh|date=2018-09-05|website=Birth.Movies.Death.|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>, [[Slamdance Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slamdance2019.eventive.org/schedule/5c1c0bd934d66c00225a9ea6|title=Hair: The Story of Grass|last=|first=|date=|website=Slamdance 2019|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thewrap.com/steven-soderbergh-to-receive-2019-founders-award-at-slamdance-festival/|title=Steven Soderbergh to Receive Founders Award at Slamdance Festival|date=2018-12-11|website=TheWrap|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref> New Filmmakers LA Monthly Film Festival<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newfilmmakersla.com/events/event/monthly-film-festival-july-27th-2019/|title=Monthly Film Festival \u2013 July 27th, 2019|website=LA Film Festival NewFilmmakers Los Angeles|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref> and the [[Red Sea International Film Festival]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.redseafilmfest.com/film?id=79|title=Hair: The Story of Grass - RedSeaFF2020|last=Apps|first=77|website=www.redseafilmfest.com|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. Her short film ''\"Cycle of Apples\" (2019)'' screened at New Filmmakers LA Monthly Film festival, which was hosted by The [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]] in partnership with Arab Film and Media Institute (AFMI)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newfilmmakersla.com/events/event/monthly-film-festival-december-14th-2019/|title=Monthly Film Festival \u2013 December 14th, 2019|website=LA Film Festival NewFilmmakers Los Angeles|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>. The film is a collaboration with American electronic opera composer [[Alice Shields]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iscm.org/catalogue/composers/shields-alice|title=Shields, Alice|last=ISCM|date=2019-07-31|website=ISCM|language=en|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://studio300.transy.edu/digital-media/creators/|title=Creators \u2013 Studio 300|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-28}}</ref>.\n\n\n\nAl-Saati's feature film project \"A Trip to Disney\" is in development with the Red Sea Film Lodge (part of Saudi Arabia's [[Red Sea International Film Festival]]), in partnership with Italy's [[TorinoFilmLab]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.torinofilmlab.it/news/640-announcing-the-12-selected-projects-for-the-red-sea-lodge-2019|title=Announcing the 12 selected projects for the Red Sea Lodge 2019! {{!}} TorinoFilmLab|website=www.torinofilmlab.it|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>''.'' She is one of the female directors that account for one-third of the 12 selected for the Red Sea Lodge, the festival said<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.screendaily.com/news/saudis-red-sea-international-film-festival-unveils-debut-lab-selection/5143374.article|title=Saudi's Red Sea International Film Festival unveils debut lab selection|last=Goodfellow2019-10-01T15:55:00+01:00|first=Melanie|website=Screen|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/news/saudi-arabia-red-sea-festival-projects-in-development-1203353478/|title=Saudi Arabia\u2019s Red Sea Festival Announces Projects in Development|last=Vivarelli|first=Nick|last2=Vivarelli|first2=Nick|date=2019-10-01|website=Variety|language=en|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>.\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Film Title\n!Arabic Title\n!Year\n!Screenings\n|-\n|Elo's Nest\n|\u0639\u0634 \u0625\u064a\u0644\u0648\n|2016\n|The 3rd Saudi Film Festival\n|-\n|Fear: Audibly\n|\u0627\u0644\u062e\u0648\u0641: \u0635\u0648\u062a\u064a\u0627\n|2017\n|Fantastic Fest, The Arab Cinema Festival at the Arab World Institute in Paris, The 4th Saudi Film Festival\n|-\n|Hair: The Story of Grass\n|\u0634\u0639\u0631: \u0642\u0635\u0629 \u0639\u0634\u0628\n|2018\n|Fantastic Fest, Slamdance, HollyShorts, Casablana Film Festival, The Red Sea International Film Festival, The 5th Saudi Film Festival\n|-\n|Cycle of Apples\n|\u062f\u0648\u0631\u0629 \u062a\u0641\u0627\u062d\n|2019\n|Oaxaca FilmFest, New Filmmakers LA\n|}\n\n== Research ==\nAl-Saati holds a PhD in Interactive Arts and Technology, from [[Simon Fraser University]] (SFU), [[Surrey, British Columbia]], [[Canada]]<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=maha+zeini+al-saati&source=bl&ots=EO8_LSmG5c&sig=ACfU3U1P-X0pBuyt6e8pu5_k0IvTiyb_bA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjsqoT_vfLnAhVfRhUIHV6ACMkQ6AEwCXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=maha%20zeini%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite thesis|title=The architectural image: space, movement and myth|url=https://summit.sfu.ca/item/13638|publisher=Communication, Art & Technology: School of Interactive Arts and Technology|date=2013-07-22|degree=Thesis|language=en|first=Maha Zeini|last=Al-Saati}}</ref>. Her PhD thesis is titled: ''\"The Architectural Image: Space, Movement and Myth\"'' (2013)<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Al-Saati|first=Maha Zeini|title=The Architectural Image: Space, Movement and Myth|url=https://www.academia.edu/7577363/The_Architectural_Image_Space_Movement_and_Myth|journal=PhD Thesis, The School of Interactive Arts and Technology, Simon Fraser University (SFU), Canada.|language=en}}</ref>, and falls within research that intersects architecture with film<ref>{{Cite journal|last=\u00a0Al-Saati, Maha Zeini; David Botta and Robert Woodbury|first=|date=|title=Moving in filmic spaces: Relating camera movements to spatial archetypes in architectural animations|url=http://papers.cumincad.org/cgi-bin/works/paper/caadria2012_013|journal=Proceedings of the 17th International Conference on Computer Aided Architectural Design Research in Asia|volume=|pages=Chennai 25-28 April 2012|via=Chennai 25-28 April 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=Al-Saati|first=Maha Zeini; David Botta and Robert Woodbury|date=2012|title=Architects on architectural film and animation|url=http://papers.cumincad.org/cgi-bin/works/Show?caadria2012_021|journal=Proceedings of the 17th International Conference on Computer Aided Architectural Design Research in Asia / Chennai 25-28 April 2012, pp. 637\u2013646|publisher=CUMINCAD}}</ref>. She is also a researcher who has written about the intersection of media, religion and culture<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PA282&lpg=PA282&dq=maha+zeini+al-saati&source=bl&ots=EO8_LSmG5c&sig=ACfU3U1P-X0pBuyt6e8pu5_k0IvTiyb_bA&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjsqoT_vfLnAhVfRhUIHV6ACMkQ6AEwCXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=maha%20zeini%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref> in her works: ''\u201cThe Protagonist Does Not Die Anymore: The Influence of the Death Narrative on Popular Saudi Culture\u201d''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Teodorescu|first=Adriana|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=u2iPDwAAQBAJ&pg=PR6&dq=maha+al-saati+Death+within+the+Text:+Social,+Philosophical+and+Aesthetic+Approaches+to+Literature,+edited+by+Adriana+Teodorescu&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjR_IOF-vHnAhXMA2MBHThHAh4Q6AEIKTAA#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=Death within the Text: Social, Philosophical and Aesthetic Approaches to Literature|date=2019-03-13|publisher=Cambridge Scholars Publishing|isbn=978-1-5275-3122-2|language=en}}</ref>''; \"A Question of Relevance: Teaching with Sci-Fi and Fantasy Film in a Saudi University\"''<ref>{{Cite book|last=Janak|first=Edward A.|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?hl=en&lr=&id=WFYYDgAAQBAJ&oi=fnd&pg=PA127&dq=maha+al-saati+protagonist&ots=wXoMqhB1uD&sig=kTJk98HExkxXU4A4XwYp5qymoSE&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati%20protagonist&f=false|title=Educating through Popular Culture: You're Not Cool Just Because You Teach with Comics|last2=Sourdot|first2=Ludovic A.|date=2017-03-01|publisher=Lexington Books|isbn=978-1-4985-4918-9|language=en}}</ref>; and the journal article ''\"Assassin's Creed : A Multi-Cultural Read\"''<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Seif El-Nasr|first=Magy|last2=Al-Saati|first2=Maha|last3=Niedenthal|first3=Simon|last4=Milam|first4=David|date=2008|title=Assassin's Creed : A Multi-Cultural Read|url=http://muep.mau.se/handle/2043/12753|journal=Loading . . .;3|volume=2|issn=1923-2691}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Winston|first=Diane|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=MCCja27G0AAC&pg=PA241&lpg=PA241&dq=The+Oxford+Handbook+of+Religion+and+the+American+News+Media+maha+al-saati&source=bl&ots=JTS1BfUQdE&sig=ACfU3U31GPn0jUDaYQ3aOw3tSyCpOR2j2g&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwjn08azl_TnAhVz8uAKHax6A8cQ6AEwAXoECAoQAQ#v=onepage&q=The%20Oxford%20Handbook%20of%20Religion%20and%20the%20American%20News%20Media%20maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=The Oxford Handbook of Religion and the American News Media|date=2012-09-06|publisher=OUP USA|isbn=978-0-19-539506-8|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|last=Young|first=Helen|url=https://books.google.com.sa/books?id=eCg_CgAAQBAJ&pg=PT207&dq=maha+al-saati&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiSoZjQl_TnAhVFA2MBHXxmBrsQ6AEIQTAD#v=onepage&q=maha%20al-saati&f=false|title=The Middle Ages in Popular Culture: Medievalism and Genre|date=2015-07-08|publisher=Cambria Press|isbn=978-1-62196-748-4|language=en}}</ref>. She has a book with French author Lily Valette ''\u201cDans le sens du poil arabe\" (2020) [English: In the Direction of Arab Hair]'' which compares the social attitudes towards body hair in Arab versus Western culture<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.lalibrairie.com/livres/le-poil-arabe_0-6236267_9791093315171.html|title=Livre : Dans le sens du poil arabe \u00e9crit par Maha Al-Saati et Lily Valette - Orients|language=fr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.culture.leclerc/livre-u/arts-culture--societe-u/sciences-humaines-u/ethnologie-u/le-poil-arabe-9791093315171-pr|title=Dans le sens du poil arabe|last=E.Leclerc|first=Dans le sens du poil arabe-Lily Valette- 9791093315171- Espace Culturel|website=Espace Culturel E. Leclerc|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gibert.com/le-poil-arabe-11464541.html|title=Ldans le sens du poil arabe|website=www.gibert.com|language=fr|access-date=2020-02-27}}</ref>.\n\n== Extra Links ==\n[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vi0NOdfzv08 France24 Arabic's interview with Maha Al-Saati on Fear: Audibly | July 10, 2018]\n\n[https://birthmoviesdeath.com/2017/10/04/fantastic-fest-shorts-fear-audibly-and-the-mysterious-emotions-of-sound Birth.Movies.Death: Fantastic Fest Shorts: FEAR AUDIBLY And The Mysterious Emotions Of Sound By Siddhant Adlakha | October 4, 2017\u00a0]\n\n[https://filmthreat.com/reviews/hair-the-story-of-grass/ Film Threat: HAIR: THE STORY OF GRASS By Enrique Acosta | September 26, 2019]\n\n[https://kawa-news.com/en/maha-el-saati-the-fantastic-ufo-from-saudi-experimental-cinema/ Maha El Saati, the fantastic UFO from Saudi experimental cinema By Kawa News | February 11, 2019]\n\n[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HEkEUIv-jGY MovieMaker's Stage 5 interview with Maha Al-Saati on Hair: The Story of Grass | August 20, 2019]\n\n[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mFL4qwtXUMU&list=PLWaYWJqhe6ajHt-dCIa17ZoX9H5-5QYmL&index=1 MovieMaker's Stage 5 interview with vocalist Zeina Nassereddine on Maha Al-Saati's Cycle of Apples | March 10, 2020]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{morecat|date=April 2020}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Al-Saati, Maha}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n", "name_user": "IndieSaudiFilm", "label": "safe", "comment": "bullet points", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maha_Al-Saati"}
